                        </origin>
                        <provenance>The manuscript was probably transferred to <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100078">Stockholm</placeName> and <placeName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/place/100089">Uppsala</placeName> during the dissolution of the monasteries (finished in <date when="1619"/>) and finally ended up in the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName>. </provenance>
                        <provenance>There are two signa found in the manuscript, one on <locus from="1" to="1" scheme="pages"/> and another on <locus from="28" to="28" scheme="pages"/>. The older signum <quote>10</quote> is found in the inventory from the 1720s (U 90:4, p. 66). Current signum, ‘A 55’, first established in Helin’s catalogue from the 1720s (U 91:2:2).</provenance>
                        <acquisition>From the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100059">Antiquities Archive</orgName> to the <orgName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/org/100004">National Library</orgName> in <date when="1780"/>. </acquisition>
                    </history>
